UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Walter S. SULLIVAN, Appellee. No. 7950. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 19, 1935. See, also, 74 F.(2d) 799. J. A. Carver., U. S. Atty., and E. H. Castcrlin and Frank Griffin, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Boise, Idaho, for the United States. Hawley & Worthwine, of Boise, Idaho, for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
